  "description": "Country Pop singer Patsy Cline performed at the The Mint Las Vegas in Downtown Las Vegas during November and December 1962. She was the first major country singer to perform in Vegas. She received great reviews at her shows. A return trip in early 1963 was in the works, however, Patsy was killed in a private plane crash in March 1963. Today the Mint casino site is Binion's Gambling Hall and Hotel .",
